[3] Israel, MOH update
Date: Thu 17 Mar 2022
Source: Israeli MOH [in Hebrew, machine trans., edited]
https://www.gov.il/he/departments/news/17032022-01


Vaccines given by breastfeeding stations of the Ministry of Health, the Jerusalem Municipality and some by Leumit:
- Vaccinated from the beginning of the operation until now: 11 785
- Vaccinated today ([17 Mar 2022]) until 14:00: 349

To date, positive / suspicious samples for the poliovirus (polio) in Jerusalem and the surrounding area:
- Children with a positive culture and symptoms: 1 not vaccinated
- Children with a positive culture without symptoms: 1 not vaccinated
- Suspicious and asymptomatic initial examination (final culture has not yet been obtained): 5 unvaccinated

All cases in which fecal polio is found are not vaccinated.

In addition, there are preliminary findings in sewage sampling of the virus in Beit Shemesh, Modi'in Illit, and Tiberias. The Ministry of Health is conducting additional tests to confirm the initial findings.

The Ministry of Health again calls on parents to make sure that their children are vaccinated according to the Ministry of Health's vaccination routine and to vaccinate the children who have not yet been vaccinated as soon as possible. The poliovirus vaccine is the most effective and safest way to prevent infection with the virus and to protect against the disease.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED

[It appears as though there is ongoing transmission of the cVDPV3 in Israel, including in locations outside of Jerusalem: Tiberias, 177.8 km (110.5 mi) by road to the north (117 km/72.7 mi as the crow flies); Modi'in Illit, 39.6 km (24.6 mi) to the northwest of Jerusalem; and Beit Shemesh, 35.7 km (22.2 mi) by road to the west of Jerusalem. There are also an additional 5 suspected cases. A map showing Israel and the Palestinian Authority can be found at https://www.worldometers.info/img/maps/israel_political_map.gif.

We await further information as it becomes available.

- Mod.MPP]
